From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: mbt28 <btekbas@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/6] media: cedrus: make VE_MODE DRAM configuration
 variant-specific

cedrus_engine_enable() unconditionally sets VE_MODE_REC_WR_MODE_2MB
(bit 20) and VE_MODE_DDR_MODE_BW_128 (bits 17:16) - the existing FIXME
already notes this is "only valid on 32-bits DDR's".

The BSP (libVE) derives those bits from the DRAM type: bits 17:16 step
through 00/01/10/11 from DDR1-16bit up to DDR3-32bit, and bit 20 is set
only together with the DDR3 encoding (VeSetDramType).  On the suniv
F1C100s family - which feeds the VE from an in-package 16-bit DDR - the
BSP never programs the field at all and even skips restoring it after
an engine reset (resetDecAndEnc early-returns for engine revision
0x1663), leaving the power-on default of all-zero.

Add CEDRUS_QUIRK_NO_DRAM_MODE_CONFIG so a variant can keep the DRAM
configuration field at its hardware default instead of the DDR3-32bit
values.  No functional change for existing variants.

Signed-off-by: mbt28 <btekbas@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/staging/media/sunxi/cedrus/cedrus.h    |  1 +
 drivers/staging/media/sunxi/cedrus/cedrus_hw.c | 12 +++++++++---
 2 files changed, 10 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/staging/media/sunxi/cedrus/cedrus.h
+++ b/drivers/staging/media/sunxi/cedrus/cedrus.h
@@ -40,6 +40,7 @@
  * programs by default, without being tied to a decoding capability.
  */
 #define CEDRUS_QUIRK_EXTERNAL_PRED_BUFFERS	BIT(0)
+#define CEDRUS_QUIRK_NO_DRAM_MODE_CONFIG	BIT(1)
 
 enum cedrus_irq_status {
 	CEDRUS_IRQ_NONE,
--- a/drivers/staging/media/sunxi/cedrus/cedrus_hw.c
+++ b/drivers/staging/media/sunxi/cedrus/cedrus_hw.c
@@ -38,9 +38,16 @@
 	/*
 	 * FIXME: This is only valid on 32-bits DDR's, we should test
 	 * it on the A13/A33.
+	 *
+	 * The suniv F1C100s family feeds the VE from an in-package
+	 * 16-bit DDR; its BSP (libVE) never sets these bits on that
+	 * engine revision (0x1663) and leaves the whole DRAM
+	 * configuration field at its power-on default of zero.
 	 */
-	reg |= VE_MODE_REC_WR_MODE_2MB;
-	reg |= VE_MODE_DDR_MODE_BW_128;
+	if (!(ctx->dev->quirks & CEDRUS_QUIRK_NO_DRAM_MODE_CONFIG)) {
+		reg |= VE_MODE_REC_WR_MODE_2MB;
+		reg |= VE_MODE_DDR_MODE_BW_128;
+	}
 
 	switch (ctx->src_fmt.pixelformat) {
 	case V4L2_PIX_FMT_MPEG2_SLICE:
